---
description: Rails 8 Model Rules
globs:
  - "app/models/**/*.rb"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Models

- Always define enums AFTER associations and BEFORE validations
- Enum syntax for Rails 8: 
  `enum :region, { northern: 0, central: 1, southwest: 2 }, validate: true`
  NOT the old hash rocket syntax: `enum region: { northern: 0 }`
- Always add validations for presence on required fields
- Always validate inclusion for enums (Rails 8 validate: true handles this)
- Association declarations order: belongs_to, has_many, has_one, has_many :through
- Always specify `dependent: :destroy` or `dependent: :nullify` on has_many
- Use `inverse_of` on associations to avoid N+1 queries
- Scopes always use lambda syntax: `scope :recent, -> { order(created_at: :desc) }`
- Never put business logic in models — use service objects